 religious groups' public roles goes beyond pessimists' fears that these groups promote culture wars, as well as optimists' expectations that religious groups are always good for society. Touching on themes as old as the American republic, this work brings into focus an urgent, current discussion that will be of great interest to students of religion and society, public religion, civil society, or religion and politics, as well as to religious leaders and policymakers.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology of Religion.2bisacsh1 aAmmerman, Nancy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChaves, Mark, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLichterman, Paul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLichterman, Paul, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMcRoberts, Omar M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMoon, Dawne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPotts, C. Brady, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPotts, C. Brady, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSchudson, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150362695940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503626959423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781503626959/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles